Ultrasonographic diagnosis of cul-de-sac endometriosis. Fifty-six women with endometriosis were examined for cul-de-sac endometriosis by ultrasonography and laparoscopy. Ultrasonographic cul-de-sac findings were classified into 3 groups i.e. Group A (n = 21): no remarkable findings, Group B (n = 16): several nodular hyperechoic or cystic hypoechoic areas, and Group C (n = 19): multiple nodular or cystic areas and/or discontinuation of the contour of the posterior uterine wall. Laparoscopic cul-de-sac findings were classified into 3 groups